  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was carried out as a numerical-simulation (high-fidelity parametric sweep). The narrative presents the simulation as functionally equivalent to bench-top experimental measurement, but the structured activityType field records numerical-simulation rather than experimental-validation, breaking the inference link required by W-AR-03.",
