      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — parametric numerical sweep",
      "description": "Hemolysis index (HI) predictions were compared against reference values across five flow-speed operating points. The supporting activity performed a high-fidelity parametric numerical simulation sweep spanning the full VAD operating envelope, with Monte Carlo sampling on viscosity and inlet boundary conditions. The resulting HI predictions fall within 8% of the reference dataset mean, which the assessment team argues is as good as experimental scatter observed in published bench-top studies. The activity is recorded as numerical-simulation; the requirement mandating experimental-validation is thereby not formally satisfied, though the narrative frames the two approaches as functionally interchangeable.",
