    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-dr-01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the high-fidelity parametric numerical simulation sweep achieves hemolysis index agreement within 8% of the reference dataset, which the team argues is comparable to experimental measurement uncertainty reported in the literature. The team concluded that the simulation evidence is as good as experimental validation for this operating regime. However, the governing requirement (vad-hemolysis-experimental-req) explicitly mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method, and the supporting activity activityType is recorded as numerical-simulation. This mismatch breaks the formal inference link under W-AR-03; the acceptance decision is therefore not fully supported by the structured evidence chain.",
